<h1>George W. Bush<i> (111552413)</i></h1><h3><i> 2006-01-31 - Speeches</i></h3>  Third, we need to encourage <a href='t9.html'><span title='9'><t9>children</t9></span></a> to take more <a href='t9.html'><span title='9'><t9>math</t9></span></a> and <a href='t9.html'><span title='9'><t9>science</t9></span></a>, and to make sure those <a href='t9.html'><span title='9'><t9>courses</t9></span></a> are rigorous enough to compete with other <a href='t6.html'><span title='6'><t6>nations</t6></span></a>. We've made a good <a href='t9.html'><span title='9'><t9>start</t9></span></a> in the early <a href='t9.html'><span title='9'><t9>grades</t9></span></a> with the <a href='t9.html'><span title='9'><t9>No</t9></span></a> <a href='t9.html'><span title='9'><t9>Child</t9></span></a> Left Behind <a href='t9.html'><span title='9'><t9>Act</t9></span></a>, which is raising <a href='t9.html'><span title='9'><t9>standards</t9></span></a> and lifting <a href='t9.html'><span title='9'><t9>test</t9></span></a> <a href='t9.html'><span title='9'><t9>scores</t9></span></a> across our <a href='t5.html'><span title='5'><t5>country</t5></span></a>. <a href='t5.html'><span title='5'><t5>Tonight</t5></span></a> I propose to train 70,000 high <a href='t9.html'><span title='9'><t9>school</t9></span></a> <a href='t9.html'><span title='9'><t9>teachers</t9></span></a> to lead Advanced Placement <a href='t9.html'><span title='9'><t9>courses</t9></span></a> in <a href='t9.html'><span title='9'><t9>math</t9></span></a> and <a href='t9.html'><span title='9'><t9>science</t9></span></a>, bring 30,000 <a href='t9.html'><span title='9'><t9>math</t9></span></a> and <a href='t9.html'><span title='9'><t9>science</t9></span></a> <a href='t9.html'><span title='9'><t9>professionals</t9></span></a> to teach in <a href='t9.html'><span title='9'><t9>classrooms</t9></span></a>, and give early <a href='t9.html'><span title='9'><t9>help</t9></span></a> to <a href='t9.html'><span title='9'><t9>students</t9></span></a> who